The article announces the 20 finalists of the Joining Forces Community Challenge, a program initiated by First Lady Michelle Obama and Dr. Jill Biden to recognize and celebrate individuals, communities, and organizations that have shown exceptional support for military families and veterans. The finalists were chosen from over 300 submissions and include organizations such as the Pat Tillman Foundation, The Sisterhood of the Traveling BDUs, and Brides Across America. The winners will be announced in the spring, with one being chosen as the People's Choice Winner based on public voting. The panel of judges includes Tom Brokaw, J.R. Martinez, Sloan D. Gibson, Mayor Julian Castro, and Deanie Dempsey. The First Lady and Dr. Biden will honor the finalists at the White House and highlight their work. The Joining Forces initiative aims to encourage all Americans to support the military and serve military families.